WEBVTT

03:53.776 --> 03:54.911
Good morning.

03:56.478 --> 03:57.479
Lovely day, is it not?

03:58.581 --> 03:59.649
What can I do for you?

04:01.884 --> 04:03.953
I know it's been quite some
time since you sold to anyone,

04:03.986 --> 04:05.822
or traded for that matter.

04:05.855 --> 04:06.756
I'm not selling.

04:07.990 --> 04:09.491
But how about a trade?

04:09.524 --> 04:10.993
I have some goods that
my wife put together.

04:11.027 --> 04:12.061
I can't spare it.

04:15.798 --> 04:17.432
You're not the
least bit curious?

04:18.935 --> 04:20.502
I don't need
anything from you.

04:23.606 --> 04:24.539
Please.

04:25.608 --> 04:26.541
I have a family.

04:30.613 --> 04:31.914
They're not my responsibility.

04:42.658 --> 04:43.860
You're very luck out here.

04:46.494 --> 04:47.429
So peaceful.

04:50.166 --> 04:51.466
Miles away from anyone.

04:55.037 --> 04:55.938
You should go.

05:02.444 --> 05:03.946
Perhaps I'll see
you again sometime.

05:07.583 --> 05:08.516
God bless.

05:33.541 --> 05:34.509
Who's that?

05:34.542 --> 05:35.978
He's a villain.

05:36.012 --> 05:37.445
Why?

05:37.479 --> 05:39.882
He steals girls like you,

05:39.916 --> 05:42.450
takes them away from
their mother forever.

05:42.484 --> 05:44.552
That's why they can
never know about you.

06:22.591 --> 06:24.794
Look how radiant you skin is.

06:28.998 --> 06:30.199
That feels good.

06:31.901 --> 06:33.501
The others will be so impressed.

06:51.754 --> 06:52.989
Why not help that man today?

06:56.659 --> 06:57.593
He's dangerous.

06:59.195 --> 07:00.495
Because he's desperate?

07:01.764 --> 07:02.798
He said he has a family.

07:04.133 --> 07:05.167
And if I helped him,
how could I refuse

07:05.201 --> 07:06.202
the next person, right?

07:07.770 --> 07:08.804
No exceptions.

07:10.306 --> 07:11.741
I suppose.

07:44.907 --> 07:45.841
Goodnight.

08:20.276 --> 08:22.244
These are dire times, indeed.

08:23.779 --> 08:26.849
To lose a life at
such a young age,

08:26.882 --> 08:30.186
is a tragedy no parent
should ever endure.

08:33.688 --> 08:34.924
Liam was my grandson,

08:34.957 --> 08:39.195
so this is an
especially hard day.

08:42.765 --> 08:45.768
But there is not a
single soul among us

08:48.437 --> 08:50.773
who could fathom
the depths of pain

08:50.806 --> 08:53.309
that the boys parents are
feeling at this very moment.

08:54.677 --> 08:55.611
Bridget,

08:57.012 --> 08:57.980
Colm, my son,

08:59.248 --> 09:01.050
I am so sorry for your loss.

09:03.152 --> 09:05.988
It might feel like this pain
will never pass, but it does.

09:07.223 --> 09:08.157
It will.

09:11.193 --> 09:13.295
And we will be here
for you both all of us.

09:19.001 --> 09:22.304
We will not allow
this time of darkness

09:23.973 --> 09:26.408
to extinguish the
everlasting light we have

09:27.810 --> 09:29.678
in our Lord Jesus Christ.

09:30.779 --> 09:33.115
Amen.

09:45.261 --> 09:47.229
How's your
William doing?

09:47.263 --> 09:49.198
No, Colm, don't.

09:49.231 --> 09:50.900
Colm.

09:50.933 --> 09:53.169
Whoa, whoa, whoa, stand.

09:53.202 --> 09:54.937
- Stand.
- Go home.

09:54.970 --> 09:55.938
- Forgive me.
- You must truly

09:55.971 --> 09:57.840
regard us as lower than dirt.

09:57.873 --> 09:59.175
- I beg your pardon.
- You see that?

09:59.208 --> 10:00.943
My wife and I buried
our son today.

10:00.976 --> 10:02.411
Well, then my
condolences to you both.

10:02.444 --> 10:05.314
You don't give a damn
about anybody at all!

10:05.347 --> 10:06.715
- Don't touch me.
- Or what?

10:07.983 --> 10:08.951
Or what, or what?

10:08.984 --> 10:10.319
Speak up, speak up!

10:11.453 --> 10:12.421
Speak up!

10:13.889 --> 10:15.357
You come through here
parading your abundance

10:15.391 --> 10:17.193
on the day of my son's funeral!

10:17.226 --> 10:18.861
I wasn't aware of the funeral.

10:18.894 --> 10:20.062
Flaunt it in front of
all these starving people!

10:20.095 --> 10:21.830
That was not my intent.

10:21.864 --> 10:23.032
We are the faithful ones.

10:23.065 --> 10:25.234
Yet, God smiles upon
you why is that?

10:25.267 --> 10:27.036
God's got nothing
to do with it.

10:28.904 --> 10:30.372
Everyone knows
what you are, Devil.

10:30.406 --> 10:32.374
Everyone knows what you are.

10:32.408 --> 10:34.043
- You creature.
- Please go!

10:34.076 --> 10:35.244
- Everyone knows.
- Keep away from there!

10:35.277 --> 10:36.812
Keep them, get away!

10:36.845 --> 10:38.247
Get away all of you!

10:38.280 --> 10:41.217
Get away, get away, get away!

10:41.250 --> 10:42.985
Get off, get off there!

10:43.018 --> 10:44.954
- Get off there!
- That's enough!

10:44.987 --> 10:46.755
Return those to Miss Earnshaw.

10:54.463 --> 10:55.931
Are you all right?

10:57.333 --> 10:58.234
Thank you.

11:12.915 --> 11:15.517
You heard
what the man said?

15:12.387 --> 15:13.690
Colm Dwyer?

15:13.723 --> 15:16.225
He cursed her out
then he hit her.

15:16.258 --> 15:17.292
Despicable.

15:19.361 --> 15:20.262
I want to help.

15:22.130 --> 15:24.266
Make him regret it.

15:24.299 --> 15:25.768
He deserves it.

15:25.802 --> 15:27.035
But keep it secret.

15:30.372 --> 15:31.306
I wouldn't know how.

15:33.108 --> 15:34.076
Well, Darling,
what you have to do

15:34.109 --> 15:36.211
is you go to Colm's house,

15:36.245 --> 15:38.146
and you get something
from his son.

15:38.180 --> 15:39.314
We'll use it in the ingathering

15:39.348 --> 15:41.450
for our little
ceremony, all right.

15:42.518 --> 15:44.119
Don't tell your mom.

15:49.659 --> 15:50.559
Thank you.

15:58.835 --> 16:00.269
What was that all about?

16:00.302 --> 16:01.236
Nothing.

16:04.406 --> 16:05.307
Come on, let's go.

16:24.627 --> 16:27.162
- What is it?
- I have to pee.

16:46.348 --> 16:49.284
Hurry up or you'll have to
hold it the rest of the way.

16:49.318 --> 16:51.320
Otherwise you'll force
me back into the box?

16:51.353 --> 16:52.254
That's right.

16:53.856 --> 16:56.291
Would you say that to me
if I was the man who hit you?

16:58.861 --> 17:00.295
What do you want?

17:00.329 --> 17:02.431
I want to help, I'm ready.

17:02.464 --> 17:03.666
This is not the time
for that conversation...

17:03.700 --> 17:06.401
Both of those men threatened
you because they're unlucky.

17:06.435 --> 17:07.469
They think you're the villain.

17:07.502 --> 17:09.906
Who do you trust, them or me?

17:14.944 --> 17:16.679
Pardon my intrusion.

17:24.286 --> 17:25.588
It's Mr. Buckley, isn't it?

17:27.222 --> 17:28.156
Yes.

17:37.834 --> 17:38.768
Here.

17:41.303 --> 17:42.537
Here please take this.

17:44.607 --> 17:45.708
Uh.

17:47.744 --> 17:50.847
Please, sir, this
does not concern you.

17:54.549 --> 17:56.184
You're welcome to it all.

17:57.787 --> 17:59.789
What, everything?

17:59.822 --> 18:00.757
Everything.

18:07.930 --> 18:10.465
Just as long as you forget
what you have seen here today.

18:15.838 --> 18:17.406
It's settled then.

18:19.776 --> 18:21.611
Please, sir, this is
not as it appears.

18:22.912 --> 18:25.547
Oh, no, what is
it then, exactly?

18:27.549 --> 18:29.619
Sir, please take it.

18:29.652 --> 18:30.552
Let us be.

18:31.888 --> 18:32.822
Please.

18:38.260 --> 18:39.294
Here.

18:39.327 --> 18:40.495
No, no, that's enough.

18:40.529 --> 18:41.563
No.

18:41.597 --> 18:43.265
No, no that's enough I said!

18:44.332 --> 18:45.267
Goddamn you.

18:49.471 --> 18:50.372
I never seen you.

18:51.473 --> 18:53.475
Thank you.

18:54.977 --> 18:55.912
Thank you.

19:16.364 --> 19:17.299
He'll talk.

19:18.467 --> 19:21.536
No matter his
promises, it'll spread.

19:23.305 --> 19:24.841
That's how it works
with these people.

19:35.618 --> 19:36.551
Audrey?

19:37.887 --> 19:38.821
Audrey?

19:42.091 --> 19:43.025
Audrey?

19:44.359 --> 19:45.360
Audrey?

21:59.061 --> 22:00.596
Listen.

22:00.630 --> 22:02.198
I got you, Love.

22:11.539 --> 22:13.009
You're safe now.

22:13.042 --> 22:14.777
Come here.

22:14.810 --> 22:16.012
Now watch.

22:16.045 --> 22:16.979
You.

22:21.250 --> 22:22.184
Okay.

22:59.922 --> 23:00.923
Bridget, love.

23:03.960 --> 23:06.829
Bridget.

23:15.871 --> 23:17.239
Goodnight then.

23:29.251 --> 23:31.654
We must keep our voices low.

23:32.788 --> 23:34.957
My wife she's asleep upstairs.

23:34.991 --> 23:35.891
Your wife?

23:36.959 --> 23:38.127
Yeah.

23:38.160 --> 23:40.062
- Bridget.
- Bridget?

23:44.767 --> 23:45.668
What's your name?

23:46.936 --> 23:48.270
I'm Colm Dwyer.

23:50.039 --> 23:50.973
And you?

23:52.274 --> 23:53.209
Audrey.

23:54.276 --> 23:55.211
Audrey.

23:57.813 --> 23:59.982
What were you doing out there?

24:02.785 --> 24:03.686
Who's Liam?

24:06.022 --> 24:06.956
Our son.

24:13.129 --> 24:14.897
What age is he?

24:17.033 --> 24:17.967
He.

24:20.302 --> 24:21.237
Passed.

24:24.607 --> 24:25.775
What happened?

24:27.043 --> 24:27.977
Fell ill.

24:31.947 --> 24:33.616
It was his breathing.

24:35.951 --> 24:37.787
The funeral must
have been very hard for you.

24:39.288 --> 24:40.856
That's how we'll be known now,

24:43.225 --> 24:44.794
the parents who
lost their child.

24:47.797 --> 24:48.764
It'll be our legacy.

24:48.798 --> 24:49.698
Your legacy?

24:51.167 --> 24:53.669
Perhaps it's strange
for me to put it that way.

24:56.872 --> 24:59.742
Maybe not, I don't know.

24:59.775 --> 25:00.943
At least you
still have Bridget.

25:04.346 --> 25:06.315
I don't know what I'd
do if I lost her too.

25:10.252 --> 25:11.353
Why were you out there?

25:13.255 --> 25:15.024
Where'd you come from?

25:22.098 --> 25:23.666
Right.

25:23.699 --> 25:24.633
It's late.

25:27.236 --> 25:29.371
You can sleep there tonight.

25:35.010 --> 25:35.945
Colm.

25:37.113 --> 25:38.047
Yes.

25:47.690 --> 25:49.091
Thank you for letting me in.

25:57.900 --> 25:59.135
Goodnight then.

26:34.203 --> 26:35.137
Bridget.

26:40.776 --> 26:41.777
Bridget.

