Bridget.

27:28.090 --> 27:29.024
Bridget.

27:30.092 --> 27:31.026
Bridget.

27:32.094 --> 27:33.329
Bridget.

27:33.362 --> 27:34.863
Bridget.

27:34.897 --> 27:35.831
Bridget.

27:37.333 --> 27:38.434
Bridget.

27:38.467 --> 27:39.535
Bridget.

27:39.568 --> 27:40.869
Bridget.

27:40.903 --> 27:42.204
Bridget.

27:42.238 --> 27:43.872
Bridget.

27:43.906 --> 27:45.074
Bridget.

27:45.107 --> 27:46.242
Bridget.

27:46.275 --> 27:47.476
Bridget.

27:47.509 --> 27:48.844
Bridget.

27:48.877 --> 27:49.945
Bridget.

28:55.044 --> 28:58.847
What the bloody
hell is wrong with her?

29:00.149 --> 29:02.418
And how
was she afterwards?

29:02.451 --> 29:05.487
Oh, she fell to sleep
once I had her back inside.

29:05.521 --> 29:06.955
You know how she is.

29:06.989 --> 29:08.524
She's always been
a tad agitated.

29:08.557 --> 29:09.858
Good morning.

29:09.892 --> 29:11.327
Bridget, love.

29:11.360 --> 29:13.362
Of course I've been agitated.

29:13.395 --> 29:14.863
He was our little boy.

29:16.298 --> 29:18.133
I'll step out for a moment.

29:23.906 --> 29:24.907
Why'd you do it?

29:29.646 --> 29:33.148
Why not ask Burke if you
wish to discuss my well being.

29:33.182 --> 29:34.483
I brought him here
to come and help you.

29:34.516 --> 29:36.218
You're not helping me!

29:36.251 --> 29:37.286
It wasn't normal what you...

29:40.089 --> 29:41.056
God.

29:42.257 --> 29:43.192
Bridget?

29:44.993 --> 29:45.928
Okay?

29:48.230 --> 29:49.398
Eh, Burke!

29:49.431 --> 29:50.366
Burke!

30:05.347 --> 30:06.348
Where were you?

30:06.382 --> 30:08.417
- Nowhere.
- Don't do that.

30:08.450 --> 30:09.686
We don't do that to each other.

30:09.719 --> 30:11.621
- What?
- Where did you go?

30:11.654 --> 30:12.655
I took a walk.

30:12.689 --> 30:13.922
To the Dwyer's house.

30:13.956 --> 30:14.957
What, no.

30:14.990 --> 30:16.024
I heard you yesterday.

30:16.058 --> 30:17.926
You spoke of him.

30:17.960 --> 30:20.129
I said you were attacked
and took it like a dog.

30:37.747 --> 30:39.616
How long have you
been feeling this way?

30:41.116 --> 30:42.585
Not long.

30:42.619 --> 30:44.319
And have you
noticed anything else

30:44.353 --> 30:45.921
that's at all out
of the ordinary?

30:48.591 --> 30:49.491
I don't believe so.

30:52.327 --> 30:54.396
I'm sure it's been a
difficult time for you both,

30:54.430 --> 30:56.365
so it does make sense
that you've missed this.

30:56.398 --> 30:57.332
But,

31:00.068 --> 31:01.403
you're with child.

31:01.437 --> 31:02.571
With child?

31:04.674 --> 31:06.375
It wasn't like this with Liam.

31:08.076 --> 31:09.344
It felt different.

31:10.512 --> 31:12.548
Every pregnancy is different.

31:12.582 --> 31:14.516
It's the reason for
your unusual cravings.

31:15.752 --> 31:17.419
Stick to proper food,

31:17.453 --> 31:20.456
and have a cup of tea if
you have any other urgings.

31:20.489 --> 31:24.126
But I'll come back in a week
or so, and we can talk more.

31:26.061 --> 31:26.962
I'll see myself out.

31:29.064 --> 31:29.965
Goodbye, Burke.

31:33.302 --> 31:34.236
I mean it.

31:36.104 --> 31:38.040
Something feels off.

31:38.073 --> 31:39.975
That's
just shock of it all.

31:41.477 --> 31:42.544
We'll take it day-by-day.

31:43.646 --> 31:44.647
Come here, Love.

31:46.515 --> 31:47.549
It'll be okay.

31:49.384 --> 31:50.620
It'll be okay.

32:09.238 --> 32:10.138
This one's done.

32:16.311 --> 32:17.446
What do you see out there?

32:19.682 --> 32:20.683
It's getting colder.

32:22.785 --> 32:24.587
All the more reason
for us to make haste.

32:26.221 --> 32:27.523
Hand me another.

32:34.631 --> 32:35.798
Christ, Audrey!

32:44.339 --> 32:46.676
I know it's all been
for my protection,

32:46.709 --> 32:47.710
everything you've done.

32:49.579 --> 32:50.479
I've tried.

32:52.414 --> 32:54.082
I know.

32:54.116 --> 32:55.484
But you need to
trust me now too.

32:57.252 --> 32:58.253
I'm ready.

33:00.289 --> 33:01.691
If that's the case,
then you'll understand

33:01.724 --> 33:03.525
the importance of sacrifice.

33:07.664 --> 33:08.564
Let me see.

33:10.432 --> 33:11.433
Mm.

33:16.706 --> 33:17.640
No.

33:32.755 --> 33:34.489
What happened here?

33:34.523 --> 33:36.626
I cannot say for certain.

33:42.732 --> 33:43.800
Fettered from the inside.

33:47.202 --> 33:48.705
It's not good.

33:48.738 --> 33:49.772
It's not good.

33:52.240 --> 33:55.243
Yeah, Lochlan's horses he's
sentimental about these things.

33:55.277 --> 33:57.512
They're not supposed
to cross species.

33:59.649 --> 34:01.383
How's our girl keeping?

34:01.416 --> 34:02.885
Oh, she's good, she's healthy.

34:07.857 --> 34:09.424
Aren't you girl?

34:10.893 --> 34:14.396
You best keep her separate
till the slaughter.

34:14.429 --> 34:15.364
Mm.

34:29.712 --> 34:30.713
What, what's wrong?

34:30.746 --> 34:31.914
- Perfectly good.
- No good.

34:33.248 --> 34:34.248
No good.

34:53.936 --> 34:57.439
Bless us, O' Lord,
with these thy gifts

34:57.472 --> 35:01.476
which we're about to
receive from thy bounty

35:02.612 --> 35:05.247
through Christ, our Lord, amen.

35:06.314 --> 35:07.249
Amen.

35:09.551 --> 35:10.485
Amen.

35:17.392 --> 35:19.361
Where did this come from?

35:21.363 --> 35:23.565
Eat up before it gets cold.

35:27.436 --> 35:28.370
Mm.

35:39.582 --> 35:40.515
Mm-mm.

36:13.750 --> 36:14.684
Mm.

36:34.402 --> 36:35.705
Come now, Mauve.

36:54.123 --> 36:55.057
Is everything all right?

36:55.091 --> 36:56.626
What?

36:56.659 --> 36:57.593
No, no.

37:00.428 --> 37:01.329
What is it?

37:02.899 --> 37:04.533
I know Bernard better
than he knows himself.

37:04.566 --> 37:05.635
There's something wrong.

37:07.136 --> 37:08.570
Ten days ago now he came home

37:08.604 --> 37:09.972
with some fresh milk and bread.

37:10.006 --> 37:11.107
Where would he get that from?

37:11.140 --> 37:12.041
He wouldn't say
where he'd found it.

37:12.074 --> 37:13.009
That can't be all.

37:16.012 --> 37:18.413
He's been fondling himself.

37:18.446 --> 37:19.481
I caught him in the act.

37:21.416 --> 37:24.486
There's something
wrong with him.

37:24.519 --> 37:26.088
This deep sadness
I can't help him.

37:26.122 --> 37:27.455
Please, Seamus.

37:31.627 --> 37:32.995
Give us a minute.

37:44.106 --> 37:45.041
May I?

37:49.045 --> 37:50.780
It's not as she
tells it, not at all.

37:53.850 --> 37:56.586
Why don't you take
it from the beginning.

37:56.619 --> 37:57.552
What brought this on.

38:00.488 --> 38:02.959
Well, you remember
how Claudia Baron died?

38:02.992 --> 38:06.829
How she grew so sick
and with the nightmares,

38:06.863 --> 38:08.898
and she blamed it
on Agatha Earnshaw.

38:08.931 --> 38:10.099
Of course.

38:10.132 --> 38:12.702
That she had a
daughter, Agatha did,

38:12.735 --> 38:14.737
a daughter that no one
had ever seen before.

38:14.770 --> 38:16.571
I questioned Agatha myself.

38:17.940 --> 38:22.044
That poor girl
withered away terrified,

38:22.078 --> 38:24.113
and not one soul
of us believed her.

38:24.146 --> 38:25.081
Well, I do.

38:26.148 --> 38:27.083
I do.

38:28.885 --> 38:31.486
Well, no, don't tell
Deirdre for God sake.

38:31.519 --> 38:32.420
Promise me that.

38:34.522 --> 38:35.825
What happened, exactly?

38:37.093 --> 38:39.862
Well, I was coming
home from a job,

38:39.896 --> 38:42.965
and it was the day
after Liam's funeral.

38:44.100 --> 38:46.035
And I passed them on the road.

38:46.068 --> 38:47.603
And I had words with Agatha.

38:48.838 --> 38:51.473
And then I seen her.

38:51.506 --> 38:52.942
I seen her.

38:52.975 --> 38:54.143
She could have
been an acquaintance?

38:54.176 --> 38:56.579
It was her
daughter I know that.

38:56.612 --> 38:58.446
I know that from the
moment I saw her,

38:58.480 --> 39:00.216
and from that same moment
when she looked at me,

39:00.249 --> 39:02.450
I had a feeling that
I never had before.

39:03.819 --> 39:05.621
Suddenly empty.

39:08.090 --> 39:09.557
What are you saying?

39:09.592 --> 39:14.130
I don't think I can
go on living like I was.

39:16.799 --> 39:17.733
Not now.

39:20.069 --> 39:23.839
She was the most
beautiful creature

39:23.873 --> 39:25.608
I've ever laid eyes upon.

39:31.647 --> 39:32.882
It's just the wind.

39:36.218 --> 39:37.153
Yes.

39:41.958 --> 39:44.593
What would
you do if he came back?

39:44.627 --> 39:46.528
Well,
I'd protect you.

39:46.561 --> 39:48.631
But what if it was the
Dwyer man from the funeral?

39:48.664 --> 39:50.199
Oh, that
wouldn't change anything.

39:50.232 --> 39:52.768
- But at the funeral...
- That was different.

39:52.802 --> 39:53.803
There was a crowd.

39:53.836 --> 39:54.704
You were in the cart.

40:02.712 --> 40:03.746
What's you legacy?

40:06.048 --> 40:07.650
Well, I'd say you are.

40:10.186 --> 40:11.954
Is one's legacy
always their child?

40:13.656 --> 40:15.091
No, sometimes it can be

40:15.124 --> 40:16.826
if someone does
something important.

40:21.263 --> 40:24.200
Then perhaps one's legacy
is how people remember you.

40:24.233 --> 40:25.567
Possibly, yes.

40:28.337 --> 40:29.939
And that could mean sacrifice?

40:31.007 --> 40:31.941
Maybe.

40:34.610 --> 40:36.746
Does that mean you'd
sacrifice yourself for me?

41:02.271 --> 41:03.973
What?

41:04.006 --> 41:06.075
- What have you done?
- Nothing.

41:06.108 --> 41:07.643
- What have you done?
- Nothing.

41:07.676 --> 41:08.911
- What have you done?
- Nothing.

41:09.979 --> 41:11.313
Get in!

41:17.019 --> 41:19.055
No, let me out!

41:20.289 --> 41:21.724
Get me out!

41:21.757 --> 41:23.759
I want out!

41:49.819 --> 41:50.753
Hello?

41:56.058 --> 41:56.992
Lochlan?

41:59.228 --> 42:00.162
Mary?

42:10.906 --> 42:11.841
Hello?

42:12.908 --> 42:13.909
Hello?

42:20.249 --> 42:21.183
God.

43:22.778 --> 43:23.946
We need to talk.

43:26.348 --> 43:29.251
We need to speak, Seamus.

43:31.120 --> 43:33.322
We need to have words.

43:35.491 --> 43:36.859
It's not normal.

43:38.761 --> 43:39.929
It's not normal.

43:45.968 --> 43:47.736
One, two good luck..

43:50.339 --> 43:53.175
We're going to be late.

43:53.209 --> 43:54.243
I'm coming!

44:05.120 --> 44:09.892
♪ Savior from all of our fears ♪

44:14.797 --> 44:19.401
♪ May angels guard
us while we sleep ♪

44:22.471 --> 44:26.141
♪ Till morning light appears ♪

44:34.383 --> 44:35.251
You may be seated.

44:40.189 --> 44:42.091
Before we get to today's sermon,

44:43.892 --> 44:45.227
I'd like to make
an announcement.

44:47.363 --> 44:50.232
Colm and Bridget are
expecting a child.

44:57.273 --> 45:01.010
I thought we should start with
a short verse from I John,

45:01.043 --> 45:03.178
chapter four verse one.

45:03.212 --> 45:07.349
"We love because
he first loved us."

45:07.383 --> 45:09.118
Short and simple,

45:09.151 --> 45:10.886
- but perhaps something...
- That's enough!

45:12.354 --> 45:14.089
How?

45:14.123 --> 45:15.424
How can you keep
saying these things

45:15.457 --> 45:17.326
and maintain a straight face?

45:17.359 --> 45:19.094
- Pardon me?
- We love.

45:19.128 --> 45:21.397
We love because
God loved us first.

45:21.430 --> 45:22.364
Is that it?

45:23.465 --> 45:24.900
It's not merely a lie.

45:24.933 --> 45:26.603
It's a great load of horse shit.

45:26.636 --> 45:27.936
You best
mind that language.

45:27.970 --> 45:29.571
No, no we're gonna
talk right now!

45:30.939 --> 45:33.108
Failed crops, sickly children,

45:34.443 --> 45:37.513
how much graver must
our circumstance become?

45:37.546 --> 45:41.517
A calf was born with
two bloody heads,

45:41.550 --> 45:45.054
and not one person
uttered a word.

45:45.087 --> 45:48.591
We're bedeviled by something
unnatural out there.

45:48.625 --> 45:50.926
And what are we doing?

45:52.061 --> 45:52.961
It's not normal.

45:54.063 --> 45:55.197
This is not normal!

45:55.230 --> 45:57.399
I'm well aware of how perverse

45:57.433 --> 46:00.202
- these tragedies have become!
- These tragedy is

46:00.235 --> 46:02.338
that we've become so complacent.

46:02.371 --> 46:04.139
We just bend over and take it.

46:04.173 --> 46:06.241
There's a
difference between complacency,

46:06.275 --> 46:07.543
and maintaining one's faith...

46:07.576 --> 46:09.111
- Faith!
- in the face of...

46:09.144 --> 46:10.479
This is not about faith!

46:12.348 --> 46:13.148
Bernard, what's going on?

46:13.182 --> 46:15.652
- Shut up!
- Put it down, Bernard.

46:15.685 --> 46:18.854
I only wish you knew
what I felt with her.

46:20.089 --> 46:21.890
I truly do.

46:21.924 --> 46:25.394
It's a strange comfort to know

46:25.427 --> 46:28.997
how truly insignificant you are.

46:29.031 --> 46:30.966
- We can talk.
- Bernard, stop.

46:32.134 --> 46:34.036
Let's step outside.

46:34.069 --> 46:36.171
- No, no!
- No, no, no, no, no, don't!

47:15.577 --> 47:17.146
What do you want?

47:20.683 --> 47:22.484
I can't be seen.

47:22.518 --> 47:23.419
Get inside.

47:51.447 --> 47:52.414
Hello?

47:53.750 --> 47:55.017
Anybody in there?

47:59.656 --> 48:01.423
What
happened to your family?

48:05.662 --> 48:07.329
We just couldn't
survive anymore.

48:09.431 --> 48:10.365
I had to do it.

48:16.238 --> 48:17.139
How do you do it?

48:18.207 --> 48:19.709
Do what?

48:19.742 --> 48:22.144
You have the only farm
producing for miles.

48:23.780 --> 48:25.481
I don't know.

48:25.514 --> 48:26.716
That's not what I've heard.

48:28.116 --> 48:29.418
What have you heard?

48:31.220 --> 48:32.689
They think it's
your heathen ways.

48:34.223 --> 48:36.158
A pact with the devil
for all that out there.

48:38.828 --> 48:40.429
Silly superstitions, I suppose.

48:45.200 --> 48:46.603
All ye had to do was
help me that day,

48:46.636 --> 48:47.704
and they'd still be here.

48:49.438 --> 48:51.039
I know you chose to insult me.

48:52.541 --> 48:53.710
I'm sorry.

48:53.743 --> 48:55.678
You knew
I was desperate.

48:57.446 --> 48:58.514
I don't want any trouble.

49:00.249 --> 49:01.183
Don't speak.

49:04.854 --> 49:08.557
Now I'm gonna take as much
as I can carry then leave.

49:08.591 --> 49:10.526
If you mention this to anyone,
I'll come back for you.

49:10.559 --> 49:13.095
I swear to fucking God I will.

49:13.128 --> 49:14.029
Do you understand?

49:18.300 --> 49:19.234
Very good.

49:20.302 --> 49:21.470
Very good.

49:50.465 --> 49:51.834
We can handle this.

49:51.868 --> 49:53.302
Well, I
could've handled it myself.

49:53.335 --> 49:54.804
He had you against the wall!

49:54.837 --> 49:56.305
He was a villain
just like you've said

49:56.338 --> 49:57.607
- about everyone!
- That's enough!

49:57.640 --> 49:58.875
They think you're weak.

49:58.908 --> 50:00.342
- And they're right!
- Watch your mouth!

50:04.781 --> 50:06.548
They will come looking for him,

50:06.583 --> 50:08.383
and sooner or later
they will find him.

50:10.485 --> 50:11.386
I saved your life.

50:15.758 --> 50:18.661
I was a fool to
think I could be the mother.

50:20.295 --> 50:21.229
Come on.

51:12.649 --> 51:14.282
What's wrong?

51:14.316 --> 51:15.818
Look.

51:15.852 --> 51:17.419
When'd that happen?

51:17.452 --> 51:18.821
I was brushing my teeth.

51:18.855 --> 51:20.690
- Let me see.
- No.

51:20.723 --> 51:21.858
- Come on let me see.
- No!

51:23.325 --> 51:24.694
I need to tell you something.

51:28.865 --> 51:30.399
I can't have this baby.

51:31.466 --> 51:32.501
What?

51:34.269 --> 51:36.606
There are ways to end a pregnancy
before it comes to term.

51:38.440 --> 51:39.909
Remedies and such.

51:39.942 --> 51:40.943
There's no way!

51:40.977 --> 51:42.544
You want to kill our child!

51:42.577 --> 51:43.680
- Colm.
- I won't allow it.

51:43.713 --> 51:44.714
- Colm, wait!
- I won't allow it!

51:44.747 --> 51:45.682
Wait!

51:46.783 --> 51:47.684
Colm, wait.

51:48.951 --> 51:49.986
No wait.

51:50.019 --> 51:52.454
Stop, listen to me I'm sorry.

51:52.487 --> 51:53.756
I wasn't aware.

51:53.790 --> 51:55.357
- You weren't aware!
- I wasn't aware!

51:55.390 --> 51:56.659
- Don't fucking touch me!
- I'm sorry please.

51:56.693 --> 51:58.795
You weren't aware
that I'd be disgusted

51:58.828 --> 52:01.229
by such a heinous proposal.

52:01.263 --> 52:03.331
The soil's not yet
settled on Liam's grave,

52:03.365 --> 52:04.801
and you're ready
to bury another!

52:04.834 --> 52:06.334
I'm sorry.

52:06.368 --> 52:07.302
- Don't touch me.
- Please don't go.

52:08.604 --> 52:09.605
Where are you going.

52:09.639 --> 52:10.907
Anywhere away from you.

52:10.940 --> 52:12.709
But you can't go, please.

52:12.742 --> 52:14.877
Please don't leave me.

52:14.911 --> 52:17.680
I can't be alone right now.

52:17.714 --> 52:18.648
Colm!

52:20.415 --> 52:21.684
Please!

53:13.936 --> 53:15.303
Come here, love.

53:37.492 --> 53:38.426
Deirdre.

53:49.939 --> 53:51.874
What did
Bernard say to you that day?

53:54.043 --> 53:55.778
- You know I can't.
- What was it?

53:57.680 --> 53:59.115
I just can't.

53:59.148 --> 54:00.783
Look something pushed
him over the edge,

54:00.817 --> 54:02.450
and I have a right to
know what that was.

54:02.484 --> 54:04.854
Look I understand
your confusion.

54:04.887 --> 54:06.454
Is there someone else?

54:06.488 --> 54:07.690
It wasn't anything like that.

54:07.723 --> 54:09.792
"What I felt with her,"

54:09.826 --> 54:11.961
he obviously wasn't
referring to me.

54:11.994 --> 54:13.729
Trust me, I'm working on it.

54:13.763 --> 54:15.497
Have you sent for help?

54:15.530 --> 54:17.432
There has to be
an investigation.

54:17.465 --> 54:19.534
- What help?
- From the cities.

54:19.568 --> 54:21.804
They can deduce his
reasoning with science.

54:21.838 --> 54:23.906
You know Bernard was
your brother-in-law.

54:23.940 --> 54:25.908
He's not just another
entry in your catalog.

54:27.576 --> 54:29.444
You want to know what
Bernard said to me?

54:34.016 --> 54:36.786
He claimed to have seen the
daughter of Agatha Earnshaw.

54:38.520 --> 54:39.789
What if he did?

54:39.822 --> 54:40.857
Have you spoken to Agatha?

54:40.890 --> 54:43.025
This requires tact.

54:43.059 --> 54:44.526
Bernard killed himself.

54:45.628 --> 54:46.596
Deirdre, please.

54:47.763 --> 54:49.765
Trust me to do the right thing.

54:49.799 --> 54:51.601
You'd better.

54:51.634 --> 54:53.669
We all deserve better than this.

54:53.703 --> 54:56.105
Bernard deserves
better than this.

55:41.918 --> 55:43.853
Hello, Agatha.

55:46.756 --> 55:48.691
May I come in?

55:48.724 --> 55:49.625
What's this about?

55:52.695 --> 55:53.796
It's important.

55:55.264 --> 55:56.165
I'll make it brief.

56:22.591 --> 56:23.491
What is it?

56:25.995 --> 56:27.129
I know it's strange,

56:28.864 --> 56:30.498
my being here.

56:30.532 --> 56:31.233
Yes.

56:34.670 --> 56:36.639
A man from my
congregation passed.

56:39.075 --> 56:40.176
It was a suicide.

56:41.744 --> 56:43.511
Oh.

56:43.545 --> 56:45.781
It happened during service
in front of everyone.

56:48.985 --> 56:51.053
He had come to me a few
weeks prior he said...

56:54.123 --> 56:56.558
He said he had seen
you and another,

56:59.962 --> 57:01.864
a girl he believed
to be your daughter.

57:01.897 --> 57:03.565
I've heard this rumor before.

57:03.599 --> 57:04.834
I remember,
but this is not...

57:04.867 --> 57:07.169
No, you don't get to
do this to me again.

57:07.203 --> 57:08.204
No.

57:09.672 --> 57:11.674
It's only due diligence
for his widow's sake.

57:12.808 --> 57:15.277
He referenced her, this girl,

57:15.311 --> 57:16.946
before he pulled the trigger.

57:16.979 --> 57:18.914
Your man was sick in the head.

57:18.948 --> 57:20.816
I will to be held accountable.

57:30.059 --> 57:31.293
Have you had another threat?

57:33.329 --> 57:34.630
Uh, no, why?

57:36.032 --> 57:36.966
There's another man.

57:38.067 --> 57:39.101
Poisoned his family.

57:40.236 --> 57:41.170
Just.

57:42.905 --> 57:44.572
Just be careful.

58:03.392 --> 58:04.860
Mr. Buckley killed himself.

58:06.962 --> 58:08.230
He saw something in you.

58:20.643 --> 58:21.343
Bridget.

58:23.913 --> 58:25.681
Bridget.

58:25.714 --> 58:26.816
Bridget, love.

58:26.849 --> 58:28.017
Bridget!

58:28.050 --> 58:29.218
Bridget, love.

58:29.251 --> 58:30.252
Bridget!

58:30.286 --> 58:31.220
Bridget.

58:41.831 --> 58:43.199
What are you doing?

58:45.401 --> 58:47.136
What are you doing?

58:49.805 --> 58:50.739
Shh.

58:51.974 --> 58:53.375
You'll wake him.

01:00:13.923 --> 01:00:14.924
What is this?

01:00:14.957 --> 01:00:15.858
We're leaving.

01:00:20.963 --> 01:00:22.298
I told you word would spread.

01:00:22.331 --> 01:00:23.899
Seamus wasn't
looking for the man.

01:00:23.933 --> 01:00:25.801
About you, Audrey.

01:00:25.834 --> 01:00:26.969
And, yes, sooner or later,

01:00:27.002 --> 01:00:27.937
they'll come looking
for the body.

01:00:27.970 --> 01:00:29.205
I can handle it if they do.

01:00:29.238 --> 01:00:30.973
It's too much.

01:00:31.006 --> 01:00:33.008
This is our home.

01:00:33.042 --> 01:00:34.877
We're going, at
least for a while.

01:00:39.782 --> 01:00:41.150
I'm not going anywhere.

01:00:47.156 --> 01:00:48.824
This isn't up for negotiation.

01:00:50.292 --> 01:00:51.193
Do you hear me?

01:00:58.434 --> 01:01:00.502
I can't believe
how weak you are!

01:01:00.536 --> 01:01:02.137
It's sickening!

01:01:02.171 --> 01:01:03.339
You'd let them walk all over you

01:01:03.372 --> 01:01:04.940
before standing your ground!

01:01:06.408 --> 01:01:08.077
What happened
to my sweet child?

01:01:09.545 --> 01:01:11.313
One of us has to do something.

01:01:38.907 --> 01:01:39.842
Audrey.

01:01:40.976 --> 01:01:42.311
Audrey, stop it?

01:01:42.344 --> 01:01:43.412
Stop it, that's enough.

01:01:43.445 --> 01:01:44.346
That's enough!

01:01:47.283 --> 01:01:48.317
You've made your point.

01:03:47.269 --> 01:03:48.270
Bridget!

01:03:51.573 --> 01:03:52.508
Bridget!

01:04:03.653 --> 01:04:04.587
Bridget?

01:04:11.628 --> 01:04:14.463
Bridget, what have you done?

01:04:14.496 --> 01:04:15.431
Huh?

01:04:21.403 --> 01:04:22.304
You didn't.

01:04:27.476 --> 01:04:29.044
What have you done?

01:04:30.212 --> 01:04:31.581
What have you done?

01:04:35.317 --> 01:04:36.218
Okay, okay.

01:04:52.067 --> 01:04:54.503
Just a wee while longer,

01:04:54.536 --> 01:04:55.437
and we'll be done.

01:04:57.072 --> 01:04:58.140
Will she be well?

01:04:58.173 --> 01:04:59.575
Yes,

01:04:59.609 --> 01:05:01.376
but she'll need
to be very careful

01:05:01.410 --> 01:05:02.679
while the stitches are in.

01:05:04.112 --> 01:05:05.013
And the child?

01:05:06.148 --> 01:05:07.282
She was very lucky.

01:05:24.233 --> 01:05:25.133
What's this?

01:05:26.468 --> 01:05:28.771
No, you don't have to do this.

01:05:28.805 --> 01:05:30.773
No, Burke, I swear I'll be
fine, no, don't do this.

01:05:30.807 --> 01:05:31.741
It's for your own good, Love.

01:05:31.774 --> 01:05:33.408
Colm, please don't.

01:05:33.442 --> 01:05:34.543
Promise I don't need this.

01:05:34.576 --> 01:05:36.746
Please, God, please don't.

01:05:36.779 --> 01:05:38.347
I'm sure it's for
your own good, Love.

01:05:38.380 --> 01:05:41.049
Colm, please don't
just stand there!

01:05:41.083 --> 01:05:43.252
I promise I don't
need this, Colm.

01:05:43.285 --> 01:05:45.588
It's only to calm
your nerves, Bridget.

01:05:45.622 --> 01:05:47.556
Please don't.

01:06:11.280 --> 01:06:12.815
Where are you going?

01:06:14.116 --> 01:06:15.050
To the others.

01:06:17.352 --> 01:06:19.054
They deserve to know
what's happened.

01:06:20.422 --> 01:06:22.157
At least they haven't
forgotten why I'm here.

01:06:28.898 --> 01:06:32.267
You'll need to keep here in
there for at least a few days.

01:06:35.404 --> 01:06:37.372
What the bloody hell
is wrong with her?

01:06:37.406 --> 01:06:38.307
I don't know.

01:06:39.474 --> 01:06:40.710
- Her temperature...
- That was not

01:06:40.743 --> 01:06:42.110
her temperature!

01:06:43.780 --> 01:06:45.715
She's gone stark-raving mad.

01:06:51.621 --> 01:06:53.422
Her heart is racing!

01:06:53.455 --> 01:06:54.356
Bridget, breathe!

01:06:56.258 --> 01:06:58.226
You need to calm down now!

01:07:21.784 --> 01:07:23.452
Well, think, damn you!

01:07:24.721 --> 01:07:25.788
That's not grieving
what she's done.

01:07:25.822 --> 01:07:27.590
What do you want me to say?

01:07:27.624 --> 01:07:28.925
She's been acting
strange for days

01:07:28.958 --> 01:07:30.760
since before we knew
she was carrying child.

01:07:30.793 --> 01:07:32.394
That's all I thought it was.

01:07:36.866 --> 01:07:38.433
Everything changed after Liam.

01:07:43.505 --> 01:07:45.474
It's been a rash of
awful business lately.

01:07:46.776 --> 01:07:47.710
Liam,

01:07:48.778 --> 01:07:49.712
now this,

01:07:50.847 --> 01:07:52.514
Lochlan and his family.

01:07:59.656 --> 01:08:00.590
Bernard.

01:08:02.424 --> 01:08:03.325
What about Bernard?

01:08:04.927 --> 01:08:06.596
You're not to utter
a word of this to anyone.

01:08:07.664 --> 01:08:08.965
Of course.

01:08:08.998 --> 01:08:11.199
He swore to me that he'd seen

01:08:11.233 --> 01:08:13.603
the daughter of Agatha Earnshaw.

01:08:16.304 --> 01:08:18.908
He passed them on the road
the day after Liam's funeral.

01:08:18.941 --> 01:08:19.876
After the funeral.

01:08:21.743 --> 01:08:24.345
He called her the most beautiful
creature he'd ever seen.

01:08:25.848 --> 01:08:26.783
I saw her too.

01:08:27.884 --> 01:08:29.283
I brought her here.

01:08:32.721 --> 01:08:36.792
I heard a scream, and then I
found her laying in the grass.

01:08:36.826 --> 01:08:38.292
Why didn't
you say something.

01:08:38.326 --> 01:08:40.562
I didn't say
anything to anyone.

01:08:40.595 --> 01:08:41.898
Not even Bridget I was so drunk.

01:08:41.930 --> 01:08:43.465
I hardly recall any of it.

01:08:47.804 --> 01:08:50.907
It all started after
that night, the sickness.

01:08:53.609 --> 01:08:54.777
She said her name was Audrey.

01:08:59.548 --> 01:09:01.283
Here.

01:09:01.316 --> 01:09:02.216
What's this.

01:09:03.586 --> 01:09:05.420
Every affliction
the village has seen.

01:09:07.790 --> 01:09:08.991
Oh, god.

01:09:10.760 --> 01:09:13.796
Everything can be traced
back to the eclipse 17 years.

01:09:15.497 --> 01:09:17.466
If Agatha's her mother,
then who's the father?

01:10:37.512 --> 01:10:38.614
God, help us.

01:11:14.016 --> 01:11:15.517
Why are you doing this?

01:11:19.121 --> 01:11:19.989
What's your purpose?

01:11:22.825 --> 01:11:24.160
My purpose?

01:11:24.193 --> 01:11:25.928
You've corrupted
my daughter-in-law.

01:11:27.797 --> 01:11:32.567
You've propelled a man from
my congregation to suicide.

01:11:37.106 --> 01:11:39.474
Why did your mother
keep you secret?

01:11:40.743 --> 01:11:41.677
